				<td colspan="2"><span>Just did the same thing you are doing now Tocatta. 
<br />

<br />
UI's - Savok's UI or Bayerithe's UI are two UI's I have been using for a very long time and I used Keiz's for awhile but I like the vert look a bit more so I changed off it.
<br />

<br />
Disc's - You can pull the discs out of the combat window and put them in your hot buttons window to avoid another window being up. I believe the tomes can be purchased at any of the wayfarer camps. 
<br />

<br />
Melody - ew. I havent messed with it that much. But I understand it breaks if you miss a note, and we all know how often that usually happens.
<br />

<br />
Bandolier - flat out owns. Basically its an in-game macro for primary/secondary/range swapping on the fly. No longer do you have to take up bag slots for instruments/weapons. Bandolier will pull the weapons/instruments directly from your bags now so you end up with more bag space lol. Believe the default to open the window is &quot;B&quot; but you can double check under the options window.
<br />

<br />
LDON has pretty much been replaced by DoN from what I understand. Missions are about the same and allows progression in faction to get some of the better missions/raids? 
<br />

<br />
I was a bit overwhelmed at first like you. Just take it alittle bit at a time and it will all be second hand to you in no time. Not that much has honestly changed. The songs we got from 66-70 are pretty much exact upgrades from what we had before. The AA that were added with OoW aren't exactly groundbreaking, so your not missing much there except the 9th spell slot now available through AA purchase.
<br />

<br />
For exp groups PoFire is still hands down the fastest xp I have heard about. Then again if you want runes for 66-70 spells your better off hitting places like Walls of Slaughter, Muramite Proving Grounds, Riftseekers(69+ only), or Nobles Causeway. 
<br />

<br />
Welcome back to EQ!
<br />

<br />
