				<td colspan="2"><span>/melody is great - you just have to work it in with twisting, depending on the circumstance.
<br />

<br />
I have almost 2 pages of hotkeys with various melody twists in them (labeled lovely names like: M1234, M2467, M3489 <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />).  I look at what's going on, and pick the best Mtwist (or best 2 or 3 options) for it and drop those hotkeys onto my pad, along with my HoS, Slow, Selo's, etc, song gems.
<br />

<br />
I use melody when I can get a regular twist going, but I'll stop it if I need to do things like HoS/slow, mez, etc.  Then I just start it up again.
<br />

<br />
For groups, I generally have a 4 twist going in /melody, since I often have to stop to pull, CC, or slow.  On raids, when I'm not pulling or helping with CC, I'll usually have a 5 twist going.  4 songs stay up steadily for me, unless the zone is very laggy.  With 5 songs, there is an occasional pause between songs, but not enough to make it an issue.  If playing resists on a raid is particularly important, I drop it back to 4 songs in melody.
<br />

<br />
Yes, breaking the melody twist for whatever reason means you need to start the /melody again.  And missed notes will indeed stop the melody, as will stuns and the like.  For the missed notes, once you fill in the anti-fizzle AA's it won't be a problem anymore.
<br />

<br />
For the rest (stopping to HoS/slow or getting stunned), I generally make sure that my important songs are at the beginning of my melody.  That's dependant on who I'm with, so it changes from group to group, and even changes depending on what the group needs atm (mana song is the one most often moved, either first or last).
<br />

<br />
Best part of Melody is that when the group needs a break to med or res, but you have a mob in the camp, you can use melody twist HoS, Mez, and Mana without killing yourself while the rest of the group go gets drinks cuz, well, they're medding and don't need to do anything.  You still have to watch, if you don't have the anti-fizzle AA's or the mob resists mez, but you don't have to have your fingers running 24/7.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
