				<td colspan="2"><span>The secret to keeping 4 regular songs up without a break (when not using /melody) on a dialup connection is to compensate for connection latency by starting Song_02 just before the cast bar empties from Song_01.  
<br />

<br />
I assume melody fails with dialup because the client (obviously) waits for a complete cast before starting the next song.  </span></td>
